
'''* Article: The Occupy Movement in Žižek’s hometown: Direct democracy and a politics of becoming. By MAPLE RAZSA AND ANDREJ KURNIK. American Ethnologist, May 2012'''

URL =  http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1548-1425.2012.01361.x/abstract [http://www.americanethnologist.org/2012/occupy-movement-zizek/]


=Abstract=

" We compare the democracy of direct action to Occupy Wall Street’s consensus-based model. In conclusion, we ask how ethnographic attention to the varieties of emergent political forms within the current global cycle of protest might extend recent theorizing of radical politics and contribute to broader efforts to reimagine democracy."
(http://www.americanethnologist.org/2012/occupy-movement-zizek/)





